Ideal System
\layout Subsection

System Description 
\layout Standard

The PC will display a continuous stream of video.
 The user will be able to stop the frame at any point, this will allow the
 user to see the most recognizable image the camera provides.
 The database information will contain a picture of the person whose PIN
 number has been typed; allowing the user to see if the picture on record
 is the same as the person attempting to use the PIN.
 If the picture is the same the visitor will have authorized access; if
 its different appropriate steps can be taken (the removal of that person
 from the premises).
 The user will then be able to communicate with the visitor and allow access
 to the site.
 
\layout Standard

When there is no user at the PC, requesting entry will enable the PC to
 reply with a recorded message of the users choosing.
 The camera will also store some frames to keep a record of who has accessed
 the site.
 Access can then be gained by a Dallas ring placed in a reader and typing
 in the correct PIN.
 The PC will contain a database of information (PIN numbers) with everything
 running through netscape.
 The system will contain a modem to allow a remote site to control the doors.
\layout Standard

Therefore a large site can be controlled by a LAN linking all of cameras
 to a centrally controlled point.
